\fs60 \cf2 What is Auto Layout?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \
Auto Layout is a system that makes it easy to support multiple screen sizes with one interface by making your interface react to changes.\
\
It does this by solving a set of layout 
\b constraints
\b0  that describe the interface of your app.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs60 \cf2 Why use Auto Layout?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \
Auto Layout makes layout code much simpler to write and maintain.\
\
Most of the time you don\'92t event have to write code.\
\
That means less time writing code and debugging it.\
\
It\'92s also easier to understand constraints than the other approaches because we generally think in language (with words) rather than in equations (with mathematics).\
\
