\fs60 \cf2 Margins\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \
Sometimes you want to add an interface component close to the side of a container but not starting from the edge.\
\
The size of that space will depend on the screen size. On an iPad you will want to leave more space than on an iPhone.\
\
Fortunately iOS has a standard margin size defined for each device.\
\
To arrange a view relative to the margin of its container all you need to do is make the constraint relative to the margin.\
\
The default margin on iOS for iPhone is 
\f1\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cb5 \{top: 8, left: 16, bottom: 8, right: 16\}
\f0\fs32 \cb1 .\
